WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.499
Information is rarely the real problem.

00:02.499 --> 00:10.659
The problem is that documents, photographs, calculations, plans,
costs, and professional observations often remain separated.

00:10.659 --> 00:16.439
A conclusion may appear clear while the evidence behind it becomes
difficult to follow.

00:16.439 --> 00:23.377
Our direction begins with a simple principle: important decisions
should preserve the path that produced them.

00:23.377 --> 00:26.677
Every record enters as a distinct piece of evidence.

00:26.677 --> 00:29.002
A plan is not the same as a photograph.

00:29.002 --> 00:31.968
An invoice is not the same as an inspection.

00:31.968 --> 00:35.264
A calculation is not the same as an observation.

00:35.264 --> 00:42.560
The system should preserve each source, its date, its context, and
its relationship to the physical property.

00:42.560 --> 00:45.934
Every source remains identifiable and traceable.

00:45.934 --> 00:49.946
The normalization layer identifies record types, aligns fields,

00:49.946 --> 00:55.247
preserves timestamps, and connects structured
information back to the original file.

00:55.447 --> 00:57.686
It does not invent certainty.

00:57.886 --> 01:02.477
It separates verified facts, missing information,
and unresolved conflicts

01:02.477 --> 01:06.995
so that a reviewer can move from an explanation directly back to the
supporting evidence.

01:07.195 --> 01:09.020
Provenance is preserved.

01:09.220 --> 01:14.569
Where a result can be calculated, the logic should remain
deterministic and testable.

01:14.569 --> 01:17.939
Defined inputs should produce reproducible outputs.

01:17.939 --> 01:24.742
Formulas, balances, costs, and comparisons should be visible rather
than hidden inside an AI response.

01:24.942 --> 01:26.999
AI should explain the logic.

01:27.199 --> 01:32.325
Artificial intelligence should explain the evidence, not quietly
replace the mathematics.

01:32.325 --> 01:34.401
Reproducibility is the requirement.

01:34.401 --> 01:42.557
AI can organize evidence, explain relationships, identify missing
context, and direct attention to what requires review.

01:42.557 --> 01:46.905
But every important statement should remain connected to its source.

01:46.905 --> 01:49.779
Verification is the filter for intelligence.

01:49.779 --> 01:57.568
The system must distinguish a verified fact from an inference, and an
inference from a question that has not yet been answered.

01:57.568 --> 02:01.902
Spatial intelligence connects digital evidence to physical place.

02:01.902 --> 02:06.386
A photograph or finding is associated with the
exact room it describes.

02:06.386 --> 02:10.871
A photograph, inspection finding, plan, cost, or construction record

02:10.871 --> 02:15.730
can be associated with the room, system, or
structural element it describes.

02:15.730 --> 02:18.607
The purpose is not virtual reality for presentation.

02:18.607 --> 02:24.424
It is a living property record that preserves what happened, where it
happened, and what supports the claim.

02:24.424 --> 02:26.694
The final checkpoint remains human.

02:26.694 --> 02:33.944
Qualified professionals must be able to inspect sources, challenge
assumptions, and request additional evidence.

02:33.944 --> 02:38.153
Reviewers must determine whether the record is sufficient.

02:38.153 --> 02:42.361
Technology supports responsibility; it does not absorb it.

02:42.361 --> 02:47.119
That is how information becomes understanding
without losing accountability.

02:47.119 --> 02:50.198
The human review is always part of the architecture.

02:50.398 --> 02:52.131
Measured Decision AI.

02:52.331 --> 02:54.602
From documents to spatial intelligence.
